<!--This is the blog posting about Definition lists. The subject matter is taken from The Barron's Business Library Textbook on Financial Management.-->
<h1>Chapter 11 on Leverage and Capital Structure</h1>

<dl>
<dt>Break-Even Analysis</dt>
<dd>This anlysis, which is closely related to Operating Leverage, determines brak-even sales - the financial crossover point at which revenues exactly match costs.</dd>
<dt>Operating Leverage</dt>
<dd>This is a measure of operating risk, arises from the comapny's use of fixed operating cost.</dd>
<dt>Financial Leverage</dt>
<dd>Thi is a measure of financial risk that arises from the presence of debt and/or preferred stock in the company's capital structure.</dd>
<dt>Total Leverage</dt>
<dd>Thi is a measure of total risk. To measure total leverage, determine how EPS(Earning Per Share) is effected by a change in sales.</dd>
</dl>
